{
  "texts": [
    "While K-means, spectral clustering, and Gaussian mixture models (GMMs) achieve similar performance on both Multi-Class and Multi-Instance accuracy, K-means, which we adopt as our default choice, is approximately 3× to 16× faster.",
    "Given this favorable speed-accuracy trade-off, we use K-means for ISAC.",
    "Automatic prompt parsingWe use an LLM-based parser to automatically extract class tokens τ i, counts n i, attributes {χ i,j }, and token relations for P repel and P bind from naturallanguage prompts.",
    "Figure 11 In all experiments, we use GPT-OSS-20B [44], which produces reliable and consistent parses in practice.",
    "For a moderately complex prompt such as \"The fluffy pillow and glass lampshade rest on the wooden nightstand by the metallic bed."
  ]
}